cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.MA, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with the challenge of providing connectivity to UAVs through existing cellular networks, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The proposed interference mitigation techniques involve signal processing and coding techniques, which are related to information theory. 
3. cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) - The paper deals with the interference problem in cellular networks, which is a core topic in communications and networking. 
4. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) - The paper proposes solutions to ensure UAVs remain in LTE coverage, which involves coordination and control of multiple agents (i.e., base stations and UAVs), which is related to multiagent systems. 
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The proposed solutions involve control and optimization techniques to mitigate interference, which falls under the scope of systems and control.
